{
  "texts": [
    "AI software is shaped by human values, which, if not carefully selected, can lead to 'good AI goes bad' scenarios (Floridi et al., 2020).",
    "Thus, the issues of the value component and ethical principles of AI use are becoming increasingly relevant.",
    "In general, the ethical issues of AI development and application are the focus of many researchers and international institutions, which has led to the creation of numerous initiatives, committees, and institutes of AI ethics.",
    "The Montreal AI Ethics Institute (MAIEI) published a guideline including the norms for responsible AI research and use (Dilhac et al., 2018).",
    "The Montreal Declaration for a Responsible Development of Artificial Intelligence is founded upon a set of ethical principles centred on seven fundamental values: well-being, autonomy, justice, privacy, knowledge, democracy, and responsibility."
  ]
}